==English==
===Etymology 1===
From Latin adjective suffix ''[[-aris]]''

====Adjective Suffix====
[[Category:English suffixes|ar]]
'''-ar'''

# of or pertaining to; adjective suffix appended to various words, often nouns, to make an adjective form.  Often added to words of Latin origin, but used with other words also.
#: ''line, linear''
#: ''alveolus, alveolar''
#: ''column, columnar''

====Usage Note====
If the root word ends in ''r'', the variant '''-al''' is often used instead.  Sometimes both forms are used: ''linear, lineal''.

